

=Description=

" In summary, in theory - there are two sorts of viable money -

1) money that's required to be valuable in itself, independent of users: it must go anywhere, so issue controlled by central authorities 

2) money whose value lies in the performance of its acceptors: it just goes around, doesn't leave its community of origin, and can be issued by any who are credible in the community"
(http://openmoney.org/dmf/theory.html)

